children.name: DOUT 1 Overcurrent
children.description: DOUT 1 Overcurrent IO element is used to indicate overcurrent on Digital Output 1. When Digital Output 1 overcurrent happens, it means that current level is > 300 mA, value is set to 1. Value 1 holds until 5 min timeout runs out. After timeout value is set to 0 if current level is < 300 mA. If current level is still > 300 mA value remains 1.

children.name: DOUT 2 Overcurrent
children.description: DOUT 2 Overcurrent IO element is used to indicate overcurrent on Digital Output 2. When Digital Output 2 overcurrent happens, it means that current level is > 300 mA, value is set to 1. Value 1 holds until 5 min timeout runs out. After timeout value is set to 0 if current level is < 300 mA. If current level is still > 300 mA value remains 1.

children.name: Pedal 1 Low Idle Switch
children.description:
Accelerator Pedal 1 Low Idle Switch

Switch signal which indicates the state of the accelerator pedal 1 low idle switch.

0 - Accelerator pedal 1 not in low idle condition
1 - Accelerator pedal 1 in low idle condition
2 - Error
3 - Not available

children.name: Pedal Kickdown Switch
children.description:
Accelerator Pedal Kickdown Switch

Switch signal which indicates whether the accelerator pedal kickdown switch is opened or closed.

0 - Kickdown passive
1 - Kickdown active
2 - Error
3 - Not available

children.name: Pedal 2 Low Idle Switch
children.description:
Accelerator Pedal 2 Low Idle Switch

Switch signal which indicates the state of the accelerator pedal 2 low idle switch.

0 - Accelerator pedal 2 not in low idle condition
1 - Accelerator pedal 2 in low idle condition
2 - Error
3 - Not available

children.name: Pedal Position 1
children.description:
Accelerator Pedal Position 1

This parameter is intended for the primary accelerator control in an application.

children.name: Pedal 2 Position
children.description:
Accelerator Pedal 2 Position

The ratio of actual position of the second analog engine speed/torque request input device (such as an accelerator pedal or throttle lever) to the maximum position of the input device. This parameter is intended for secondary accelerator control in an application.

children.name: Road Speed Limit Status
children.description:
Status (active or not active) of the system used to limit maximum vehicle velocity.

0 - Active
1 - Not Active
2 - Error
3 - Not available

children.name: Remote Acc Pedal Position
children.description:
Remote Accelerator Pedal Position

The ratio of actual position of the remote analog engine speed/torque request input device (such as an accelerator pedal or throttle lever) to the maximum position of the input device.

children.name: Rate Limit Status
children.description:
Vehicle Acceleration Rate Limit Status

Status (active or not active) of the system used to limit maximum forward vehicle acceleration.

0 - Limit not active
1 - Limit active
2 - Reserved
3 - Not available

children.name: Momentary Engine Max
children.description:
Momentary Engine Maximum Power Enable Feedback

Momentarily requesting Engine Maximum Power Enable - feature support feedback

0 - disabled
1 - supported
2 - reserved
3 - don't care

children.name: DPF Thermal Management
children.description:
DPF Thermal Management Active

Indicates that the exhaust temperatures have been elevated for regeneration of the diesel particulate filter aftertreatment system or in preparation of regeneration of the diesel particulate aftertreatment system.

0 - DPF Thermal Management is not active
1 - DPF Thermal Management is active
2 - Reserved
3 - Don't care

children.name: SCR Thermal Management
children.description:
SCR Thermal Management Active

Indicates that the exhaust temperatures have been elevated for regeneration of the SCR aftertreatment system or in preparation of regeneration of the SCR aftertreatment system.

0 - SCR Thermal Management is not active
1 - SCR Thermal Management is active
2 - Reserved
3 - Don't care

children.name: Actual Max Available Engine
children.description:
Actual Maximum Available Engine

This is the maximum amount of torque that the engine can immediately deliver as a percentage of the reference engine torque.

children.name: Estimated Pumping
children.description: The calculated torque that indicates the estimated amount of torque loss due to the engine air handling system.

children.name: Actual Engine (Fractional)
children.description:
This parameter displays an additional torque in percent of the reference engine torque.

0 - +0.000%
1 - +0.125%
...
9 - +0.875%
10 to 15 - not available

children.name: Driver’s Demand Engine
children.description: The requested torque output of the engine by the driver.

children.name: Actual Engine
children.description: The calculated output torque of the engine.

children.name: Source Address
children.description:
Source Address of Controlling Device for Engine Control

The source address of the SAE J1939 device currently controlling the engine.

children.name: Intake Temp
children.description:
Aftertreatment 1 Diesel Oxidation Catalyst Intake Temperature

Temperature of engine combustion byproducts entering the diesel oxidation catalyst in exhaust bank 1.

children.name: Outlet Temp
children.description:
Aftertreatment 1 Diesel Oxidation Catalyst Outlet Temperature

Temperature of engine combustion byproducts leaving the diesel oxidation catalyst exhaust in exhaust bank 1.

children.name: Differential Pressure
children.description:
Aftertreatment 1 Diesel Oxidation Catalyst Differential Pressure

Exhaust differential pressure measured between the intake and exhaust of a diesel oxidation catalyst in exhaust bank 1.

children.name: Intake Temp FMI
children.description:
Aftertreatment 1 Diesel Oxidation Catalyst Intake Temperature Preliminary FMI

Used to identify the applicable J1939-73 FMI detected in the diesel oxidation catalyst intake temperature sensor by the manufacturer’s sensor control software in exhaust bank 1.

A value of 31 is sent to indicate that no failure has been detected or this parameter is not supported.

children.name: Outlet Temp FMI
children.description:
Aftertreatment 1 Diesel Oxidation Catalyst Outlet Temperature Preliminary FMI 

Used to identify the applicable J1939-73 FMI detected in the diesel oxidation catalyst outlet gas temperature sensor by the manufacturer’s sensor control software in exhaust bank 1.

A value of 31 is sent to indicate that no failure has been detected or this parameter is not supported.

children.name: Differential Pressure FMI
children.description:
Aftertreatment 1 Diesel Oxidation Catalyst Differential Pressure Preliminary FMI 

Used to identify the applicable J1939-73 FMI detected in the diesel oxidation catalyst differential pressure sensor by the manufacturer’s sensor control software in exhaust bank 1.

A value of 31 is sent to indicate that no failure has been detected or this parameter is not supported.

children.name: Filter Soot Load Percent
children.description:
Aftertreatment 1 Diesel Particulate Filter Soot Load Percent

Indicates the soot load percent of diesel particulate filter 1.

children.name: Filter Ash Load Percent
children.description:
Aftertreatment 1 Diesel Particulate Filter Ash Load Percent

Indicates the ash load percent of diesel particulate filter 1.

children.name: Filter Time
children.description:
Aftertreatment 1 Diesel Particulate Filter Time Since Last Active Regeneration 

Aftertreatment 1 Diesel Particulate Filter Time Since Last Active Regeneration 

Indicates the time since the last active regeneration event of diesel particulate filter 1.

children.name: Regeneration Threshold
children.description:
Aftertreatment 1 Diesel Particulate Filter Soot Load Regeneration Threshold 

This parameter indicates the value that will first cause DPF regeneration in aftertreatment 1.

children.name: Intermediate Temp
children.description:
Aftertreatment 1 Diesel Particulate Filter Intermediate Temperature 

Temperature of engine combustion byproducts at a mid-point in the diesel particulate filter in exhaust bank 1.

children.name: Differential Pressure
children.description:
Aftertreatment 1 Diesel Particulate Filter Differential Pressure

Exhaust differential pressure measured between the intake and exhaust of a diesel particulate filter in exhaust bank 1.

children.name: Differential Pressure FMI
children.description:
Aftertreatment 1 Diesel Particulate Filter Differential Pressure Preliminary FMI

Used to identify the applicable J1939-73 FMI detected in the diesel particulate filter differential pressure sensor by the manufacturer’s sensor control software in exhaust bank 1. In the case of multiple failures the most severe is communicated.

A value of 31 is sent to indicate that no failure has been detected or this parameter is not supported.

children.name: Intermediate Temp FMI
children.description:
Aftertreatment 1 Diesel Particulate Filter Intermediate Temperature Preliminary FMI 

Used to identify the applicable J1939-73 FMI detected in the diesel particulate filter intermediate temperature sensor by the manufacturer’s sensor control software in exhaust bank 1. In the case of multiple failures the most severe is communicated.

A value of 31 is sent to indicate that no failure has been detected or this parameter is not supported.

children.name: Filter Intake Temp
children.description: Temperature of engine combustion byproducts entering the diesel particulate filter in exhaust bank 1.

children.name: Filter Intake Temp FMI
children.description:
Aftertreatment 1 Diesel Particulate Filter Intake Temperature Preliminary FMI 

Used to identify the applicable J1939-73 FMI detected in the diesel particulate filter intake temperature sensor by the manufacturer’s sensor control software in exhaust bank 1. In the case of multiple failures the most severe is communicated.

A value of 31 is sent to indicate that no failure has been detected or this parameter is not supported.

children.name: Filter Intake Pressure
children.description:
Aftertreatment 1 Diesel Particulate Filter Intake Pressure 

Exhaust pressure as a result of particle accumulation on filter media placed in the exhaust stream.

children.name: Exhaust Temp 2
children.description: The reading from the exhaust temperature sensor located midstream of the other two temperature sensors in the aftertreatment system in exhaust bank 1.

children.name: Exhaust Temp 2 FMI
children.description:
Exhaust Temperature 2 Preliminary FMI

Used to identify the applicable J1939-73 FMI detected in the exhaust temperature 2 sensor by the manufacturer’s sensor control software in exhaust bank 1. In the case of multiple failures the most severe is communicated.

A value of 31 is sent to indicate that no failure has been detected or this parameter is not supported.

children.name: Exhaust Temp 1
children.description: The reading from the exhaust temperature sensor located farthest upstream in the aftertreatment system in exhaust bank 1.

children.name: Exhaust Temp 1 FMI
children.description:
Aftertreatment 1 Exhaust Temperature 1 Preliminary FMI

Used to identify the applicable J1939-73 FMI detected in the exhaust temperature 1 sensor by the manufacturer’s sensor control software in exhaust bank 1. In the case of multiple failures the most severe is communicated.

A value of 31 is sent to indicate that no failure has been detected or this parameter is not supported.

children.name: Trip Fuel (Gaseous)
children.description: Total fuel consumed (trip drive fuel + trip PTO governor moving fuel + trip PTO governor non-moving fuel + trip idle fuel) since the last trip reset.

children.name: Total Fuel Used (Gaseous)
children.description: Total fuel consumed (trip drive fuel + trip PTO governor moving fuel + trip PTO governor non-moving fuel + trip idle fuel) over the life of the engine.

children.name: Trip Vehicle Distance
children.description: Distance traveled during all or part of a journey.

children.name: Total Vehicle Distance
children.description: Accumulated distance traveled by vehicle during its operation.

children.name: Total Vehicle Hours
children.description: Accumulated time of operation of vehicle.

children.name: Total Power Takeoff Hours
children.description: Accumulated time of operation of power takeoff device.

children.name: Percent Load
children.description:
Engine Percent Load At Current Speed

The ratio of actual engine percent torque (indicated) to maximum indicated torque available at the current engine speed, clipped to zero torque during engine braking.

children.name: Torque Mode
children.description:
Engine Torque Mode

State signal which indicates which engine torque mode is currently generating, limiting, or controlling the torque.

Mode 0 - “No request”: engine torque may range from 0 to full load only due to low idle governor output.
Modes 1 to 14 indicate that there is either a torque request or the identified function is currently controlling the engine: engine torque may range from 0 (no fueling) to the upper limit.
Mode 15 -

children.name: Speed
children.description:
Engine Speed

Actual engine speed which is calculated over a minimum crankshaft angle of 720 degrees divided by the number of cylinders.

children.name: Starter Mode
children.description:
Engine Starter Mode

There are several phases in a starting action and different reasons why a start cannot take place.

0 - start not requested
1 - starter active but not engaged
2 - starter active and engaged
3 - start finished; starter not active after having been actively engaged (after 50ms mode goes to 0)
4 - starter inhibited due to engine already running
5 - starter inhibited due to engine not ready for start (preheating)
6 - starter inhibited due to driveline engaged or other transmission inhibit
7 - starter inhibited due to active immobilizer
8 - starter inhibited due to starter over-temp
9 - starter inhibited due to intake air shutoff valve being active
10 - starter inhibited due to active emissions control system condition
11 - starter inhibited due to ignition key cycle required
12 - starter inhibited - reason unknown
13 - error (legacy implementation only, use 14)
14 - error
15 - not available

children.name: Demand
children.description:
Engine Demand

The calculated torque that indicates the estimated amount of torque loss due to the engine air handling system.

children.name: Total Hours of Operation
children.description:
Engine Total Hours of Operation

Accumulated time of operation of engine.

children.name: Total Revolutions
children.description:
Engine Total Revolutions

Accumulated number of revolutions of engine crankshaft during its operation.

children.name: Trip Fuel
children.description:
Engine Trip Fuel

Fuel consumed during all or part of a journey.

children.name: Total Fuel Used
children.description:
Engine Total Fuel Used

Accumulated amount of fuel used during vehicle operation.

children.name: Coolant Temp
children.description:
Engine Coolant Temperature

Temperature of liquid found in engine cooling system.

children.name: Fuel 1 Temp 1
children.description:
Engine Fuel 1 Temperature 1

Temperature of fuel (or gas) of the first fuel type.

children.name: Oil Temp 1
children.description:
Engine Oil Temperature 1

Temperature of the engine lubricant.

children.name: Turbocharger 1 Oil Temp
children.description:
Engine Turbocharger 1 Oil Temperature 

Temperature of the turbocharger lubricant.

children.name: Intercooler Temp
children.description:
Engine Intercooler Temperature

Temperature of liquid found in the intercooler located after the turbocharger.

children.name: Cooler Thermostat Opening
children.description:
Engine Charge Air Cooler Thermostat Opening 

The current position of the thermostat used to regulate the temperature of the engine charge air cooler.
A value of 0% represents the thermostat being completely closed and 100% represents the thermostat being completely open.

children.name: Fuel Delivery Pressure
children.description:
Engine Fuel Delivery Pressure

The current position of the thermostat used to regulate the temperature of the engine charge air cooler.
A value of 0% represents the thermostat being completely closed and 100% represents the thermostat being completely open.

children.name: Crankcase Blow-by Pressure
children.description:
Engine Extended Crankcase Blow-by Pressure

Differential crankcase blow-by pressure as measured through a tube with a venturi.

children.name: Oil Level
children.description:
Engine Oil Level

Ratio of current volume of engine sump oil to maximum required volume.

children.name: Oil Level Pressure 1
children.description:
Engine Oil Pressure 1

Gage pressure of oil in engine lubrication system as provided by oil pump.

children.name: Crankcase Pressure 1
children.description:
Engine Crankcase Pressure 1

First instance of the gage pressure inside engine crankcase.

children.name: Coolant Pressure 1
children.description:
Engine Coolant Pressure 1

Gage pressure of liquid found in engine cooling system.

children.name: Coolant Level 1
children.description:
Engine Coolant Level 1

Ratio of volume of liquid found in engine cooling system to total cooling system volume.

children.name: Idle Increment Switch
children.description:
Engine Idle Increment Switch

Switch signal which indicates the position of the idle increment switch.

0 - Off
1 - On
2 - Error
3 - Not available

children.name: Idle Decrement Switch
children.description:
Engine Idle Decrement Switch

Switch signal which indicates the position of the idle decrement switch.

0 - Off
1 - On
2 - Error
3 - Not available

children.name: Diagnostic Test Switch
children.description:
Engine Diagnostic Test Mode Switch

Switch signal which indicates the position of the engine diagnostic test mode switch.

0 - Off
1 - On
2 - Error
3 - Not available

children.name: Shutdown Override Switch
children.description:
Engine Shutdown Override Switch

Switch signal which indicates the position of the engine shutdown override switch. This switch function allows the operator to override an impending engine shutdown.

0 - Off
1 - On
2 - Error
3 - Not available

children.name: Fuel Rate
children.description:
Engine Fuel Rate

Amount of fuel consumed by engine per unit of time. 

l/h

children.name: Instantaneous Fuel Economy
children.description:
Engine Instantaneous Fuel Economy

Current fuel economy at current vehicle velocity.

km/L

children.name: Average Fuel Economy
children.description:
Engine Average Fuel Economy

Average of instantaneous fuel economy for that segment of vehicle operation of interest. 

km/L

children.name: Throttle Valve 1 Position 1
children.description:
Engine Throttle Valve 1 Position 1

The position of the valve used to regulate the supply of a fluid, usually air or fuel/air mixture, to an engine. 0% represents no supply and 100% is full supply.

children.name: Throttle Valve 2 Position 1
children.description:
Engine Throttle Valve 2 Position 1

The sensed position feedback of the valve, coming from a second electrical actuator for a second throttle plate, used to regulate the supply of a fluid, usually air or fuel//air mixture. 0% represents no supply and 100% is full supply.

children.name: Intake 1 Air Temp
children.description:
Engine Intake 1 Air Temperature

Temperature of air entering vehicle air induction system.

children.name: Intake Manifold 1 Pressure
children.description:
Engine Intake Manifold #1 Pressure

The gauge pressure measurement of the air intake manifold. If there are multiple air pressure sensors in the intake stream, this is the last one in flow direction before entering the combustion chamber. This should be the pressure used to drive gauges and displays.

children.name: Intake Manifold 1 Temp
children.description:
Engine Intake Manifold #1 Temperature

Temperature of pre-combustion air found in intake manifold of engine air supply system.

children.name: Intake Air Pressure
children.description:
Engine Intake Air Pressure

Absolute air pressure at input port to intake manifold or air box.

children.name: Air Filter 1 Pressure
children.description:
Engine Air Filter 1 Differential Pressure

Change in engine air system pressure, measured across the filter, due to the filter and any accumulation of solid foreign matter on or in the filter.

children.name: Exhaust Temp
children.description:
Engine Exhaust Temperature

Temperature of combustion byproducts leaving the engine.

children.name: Coolant Filter Pressure
children.description:
Engine Coolant Filter Differential Pressure

Change in coolant pressure, measured across the filter, due to the filter and any accumulation of solid or semisolid matter on or in the filter.

children.name: Fuel Filter Pressure
children.description:
Engine Fuel Filter Differential Pressure

Change in fuel delivery pressure, measured across the filter, due to accumulation of solid or semisolid matter on the filter element.

children.name: Oil Filter Pressure
children.description:
Engine Oil Filter Differential Pressure

Change in engine oil pressure, measured across the filter, due to the filter and any accumulation of solid or semisolid material on or in the filter.

children.name: Oil Filter Pressure (Ext)
children.description:
Engine Oil Filter Differential Pressure (Extended Range) 

Change in engine oil pressure, measured across the filter, due to the filter and any accumulation of solid or semisolid material on or in the filter.

children.name: Two Speed Axle Switch
children.description:

0 - Low speed range
1 - High speed range
2 - Error
3 - Not available

children.name: Parking Brake
children.description:

0 - Parking brake not set
1 - Parking brake set
2 - Error
3 - Not available

children.name: Pause Switch
children.description:

Switch signal which indicates the position of the Cruise Control Pause Switch used on Remote Cruise Control applications. The Cruise Control Pause Switch signal temporarily disables the Cruise Control function.

0 - Off
1 - On
2 - Error Indicator
3 - Take No Action

children.description:

Cruise control is switched on.

0 - Cruise control switched off
1 - Cruise control switched on
2 - Error
3 - Not available

children.description:

Switch signal which indicates that it is possible to manage the cruise control function.

0 - Cruise control disabled
1 - Cruise control enabled
2 - Error
3 - Not available

children.name: Set Switch
children.description:
Cruise Control Set Switch

Switch signal of the cruise control activator which indicates that the activator is in the position "set."

0 - Cruise control activator not in the position "set"
1 - Cruise control activator in position "set"
2 - Error
3 - Not available

children.name: Coast Switch
children.description:
Cruise Control Coast Switch

Switch signal of the cruise control activator which indicates that the activator is in the position "coast (decelerate)."

0 - Cruise control activator not in the position "coast"
1 - Cruise control activator in position "coast"
2 - Error
3 - Not available

children.name: Resume Switch
children.description:
Cruise Control Resume Switch

Switch signal of the cruise control activator which indicates that the activator is in the position "resume."

0 - Cruise control activator not in the position "resume"
1 - Cruise control activator in position "resume"
2 - Error
3 - Not available

children.name: Accelerate Switch
children.description:
Cruise Control Accelerate Switch

Switch signal of the cruise control activator which indicates that the activator is in the position "accelerate."

0 - Cruise control activator not in the position "accelerate"
1 - Cruise control activator in position "accelerate"
2 - Error
3 - Not available

children.description:

Value of set (chosen) velocity of velocity control system.

0 - Off/Disabled
1 - Hold
2 - Remote Hold
3 - Standby
4 - Remote Standby
5 - Set
6 - Decelerate/Coast
7 - Resume
8 - Accelerate
9 - Accelerator Override
10 - Preprogrammed set speed 1
11 - Preprogrammed set speed 2
12 - Preprogrammed set speed 3
13 - Preprogrammed set speed 4
14 - Preprogrammed set speed 5
15 - Preprogrammed set speed 6
16 - Preprogrammed set speed 7
17 - Preprogrammed set speed 8
18 - PTO set speed memory 1
19 - PTO set speed memory 2
20 - PTO set speed memory 3
21 - Reserved
22 - Reserved
23 - Reserved
24 - Reserved
25 - Reserved
26 - Reserved
27 - Reserved
28 - Reserved
29 - Reserved
30 - Reserved
31 - Not available

children.name: Park Brake Release Inhibit
children.description:

Park Brake Release Inhibit Request signals the desire that an applied park brake remain applied and limit the ability of the vehicle to be moved.

0 - Park Brake Release Inhibit not requested

children.name: Oil Level 1 Countdown
children.description:
Oil Level 1 Countdown Timer

Countdown timer for the first instance of a transmission oil level indicator. Once all vehicle conditions (such as vehicle stopped, etc) are met, some transmissions may require a 'settling time' to allow the fluid level to normalize. This parameter indicates how much of the required settling time remains.

0 - less than 1 minute
1 - One minute
2 - Two minutes
3 - Three minutes
4 - Four minutes
5 - Five minutes
6 - Six minutes
7 - Seven minutes
8 - Eight minutes
9 - Nine minutes
10 - Ten minutes
11 - Eleven minutes
12 - Twelve minutes
13 - Thirteen minutes
14 - Error
15 - Not Available

children.name: Oil Level 1 Measurement
children.description:
Oil Level 1 Measurement Status

Measurement status for the first instance of a transmission oil level indicator. If conditions are not acceptable, this parameter conveys to the operator what prevents conditions from being acceptable.

0 - Conditions valid for transmission oil level measurement
1 - Conditions not valid – Settling timer still counting down
2 - Conditions not valid – Transmission in gear
3 - Conditions not valid – Transmission fluid temperature too low
4 - Conditions not valid – Transmission fluid temperature too high
5 - Conditions not valid – Vehicle moving; output shaft speed too high
6 - Conditions not valid – Vehicle not level
7 - Conditions not valid – Engine speed too low
8 - Conditions not valid – Engine speed too high
9 - Conditions not valid – No request for reading
10 - Not defined
11 - Not defined
12 - Not defined
13 - Conditions not valid - Other
14 - Error
15 - Not available

data.description:
Teltonika TFT100
Small, professional and waterproof tracker for e-forklifts and e-scooters with internal high gain GNSS/GSM antennas, Bluetooth, high capacity internal Li-Ion battery and 10-97 V power supply range for integration variety.

Manual https://wiki.teltonika-sas.com/view/Category:TFT100_Manual
 
Commands description https://wiki.teltonika-sas.com/view/TFT100_SMS/GPRS_Commands
